Isaiah 26-6 <t>The foot tramples it, </t><t>the feet of <f>ⓕ</f>the poor, </t><t>the steps of <f>ⓖ</f>the needy.” </t>
Isaiah 26-7 <pb/><t>The path of the righteous is level; </t><t><f>ⓗ</f>you make level the way of the righteous.</t>
Isaiah 26-8 <t>In the path of your judgments, </t><t>O LORD, we wait for you; </t><t><f>ⓘ</f>your name and <f>ⓙ</f>remembrance </t><t>are the desire of our soul.</t>
Isaiah 26-9 <t>My soul yearns for you in the night; </t><t>my spirit within me earnestly seeks you. </t><t><f>ⓚ</f>For when your judgments are in the earth, </t><t>the inhabitants of the world learn righteousness.</t>
Isaiah 26-10 <t><f>ⓛ</f> If favor is shown to the wicked, </t><t>he does not learn righteousness; </t><t>in the land of uprightness he deals corruptly </t><t>and does not see the majesty of the LORD.</t>
